					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Also, the NES displays non-interlaced 60FPS video, people have since referred to it as '240p'.  On some TVs, you get black scanlines between each line, since it doesn't update the odd-numbered rows, while on other TVs, the video beam is thick enough to cover up the black and you don't get this artifact.</div>

					
