					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Okay, this is bugging the crap out of me.<br />TV's don't operate at 60 fps.  This is a misconception of how interlaced signals work.  They do not send two different frames, they have one frame that is divided into two parts.  While you could *sort of* claim that's 60 images per second, it's actually 60 half-images.  The images don't even look right by themselves; they are incomplete.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

